<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="R7-030" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Design GetConfigSchema() signature + schema DTO shape</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>3</wave>
    <estimated-effort>2-3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, planning, wave-3</tags>
    <rigor-level>STANDARD</rigor-level>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>Wave 1 complete (010)</dependencies>
    <fr-coverage>FR-16 (design portion)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wave 3 starts here. Before code lands on `INodeExecutor` or its 33 implementations, the schema DTO
    shape must be pinned: what does `GetConfigSchema()` return? FR-16 calls for a TypeScript-like
    descriptor (field types, required/optional, defaults, descriptions, optional enums). Produce a
    design doc the next tasks (031 interface change, 032 per-executor impl, 033 endpoint) can implement
    without ambiguity.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET backend developer with API design sensibility. Goal: design a JSON-serializable schema
    shape that is unambiguous, minimal, and forward-compatible (new field-type kinds added without breaking).
  </role>

  <goal>
    A design document at `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/getconfigschema-design.md`
    that pins:
    1. `INodeExecutor.GetConfigSchema()` method signature (return type, sync vs async, parameter list — likely none)
    2. The schema DTO C# record(s) (e.g., `ExecutorConfigSchema`, `ConfigFieldDescriptor`) including all members and their JSON serialization names
    3. The supported `type` values (string / number / boolean / object / array — plus optional `enum`) and what each implies for the canvas form renderer
    4. Required vs optional fields semantics (boolean `required`, nullable `default`, nullable `enum`, nullable `description`)
    5. How a placeholder/empty schema is represented (e.g., zero fields = `{}`)
    6. How the endpoint payload aggregates schemas — keyed by `ExecutorType` integer (the post-rename enum), the executor's display name, or both
    7. Forward-compat strategy when a new field type or attribute is needed without breaking existing PlaybookBuilder canvas consumers
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-doc">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="interface">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/INodeExecutor.cs</file>
    <file purpose="pattern-reference">.claude/patterns/ai/node-executor-authoring.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-16">Method returns a TypeScript-like schema descriptor: field types, required/optional, defaults, descriptions. Endpoint serves the full registry to PlaybookBuilder canvas.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI Minimalism — `GetConfigSchema()` MUST be a method on `INodeExecutor`, NOT a new abstraction layer (no `IConfigSchemaProvider` or factory wrappers). Spec explicitly notes "static attribute alternative" was considered and rejected during this design step.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — the schema endpoint is a thin facade over the executor registry; it does NOT introduce new dispatch surface area.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Testing Strategy — design must produce a shape that can be tested via plain JSON serialization assertions (no need for HttpMessageHandler mocks or DI-graph plumbing).</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Component justification triple applies to the schema DTO design:
      1. Existing: no existing `INodeExecutor.GetConfigSchema()` or `ExecutorConfigSchema` record exists.
      2. Extension: this is a method ADDED to an existing interface, not a new interface — minimum new surface area.
      3. Cost-of-doing-nothing: FR-23 (typed config forms in PlaybookBuilder canvas) cannot ship; canvas continues to require makers to hand-edit `sprk_configjson` for every node; FR-16 acceptance criterion (5 typed forms minimum) blocked.
    </constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">No publish-size or CVE impact in this task (planning only, no code change). Verified at task 036.</constraint>
    <constraint source="DO NOT CHANGE">Working endpoint name `GET /api/ai/playbook-builder/executor-config-schemas` is the spec assumption. If the design surfaces a stronger naming convention from existing PlaybookBuilder endpoints, RAISE as Open Question in the design doc — do NOT change the URL substantively without sign-off.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>ai/node-executor-authoring</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ai/node-executor-authoring.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-013-bff-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-038-testing-strategy.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="INodeExecutor interface" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/INodeExecutor.cs">
        Current shape: `SupportedActionTypes` property + `ExecuteAsync` + `Validate`. `GetConfigSchema()` joins as a third synchronous accessor.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-16 closes Invariant 5 (typed config) for the Playbook Builder canvas. Today every node's
      configuration lives as free-form `sprk_configjson` and makers must know what shape each executor
      expects. The schema endpoint lets the canvas render typed forms per executor — string fields,
      dropdowns, booleans, sub-JSON editors as needed — driven by data, not hand-coded UI per executor.
      Wave 8 task 083 consumes this endpoint to drive form rendering.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="Wave 1 (010)" status="not-started-but-required">Wave 1 completion gates Wave 3 start per WBS — but this design task only reads code; no dependency on AiCompletion existing.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 031 adds the method to the interface.</item>
      <item>Task 032 implements it on all 33 executors (5 rich schemas, 28 placeholders).</item>
      <item>Task 033 builds the BFF endpoint serving the registry.</item>
      <item>Task 083 (Wave 8) consumes the endpoint to drive typed-form rendering.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD · 📋 REASON: planning/design task, no source modification, design artifact only · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-16 + plan.md Wave 3 + `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Read INodeExecutor interface">
      Open `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/INodeExecutor.cs`. Note current member signatures and XML doc style.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Sketch candidate DTO shape">
      Draft a C# record like:
      <![CDATA[
      public sealed record ExecutorConfigSchema(
          IReadOnlyDictionary<string, ConfigFieldDescriptor> Fields);

      public sealed record ConfigFieldDescriptor(
          string Type,           // "string" | "number" | "boolean" | "object" | "array"
          bool Required,
          object? Default,
          string Description,
          IReadOnlyList<string>? Enum);
      ]]>
      Annotate with `[JsonPropertyName]` decisions and serialization examples.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Define type taxonomy">
      Enumerate the allowed `Type` strings. Decide whether `array` is in v1 or deferred. Decide how nested objects are described (recursive `Fields`? string-typed JSON sub-editor?).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Define placeholder/empty schema">
      A placeholder schema for the 28 non-priority executors should serialize as `{ "fields": {} }`. Document this is the literal placeholder.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Define endpoint payload aggregation">
      Decide aggregation shape — likely `Dictionary&lt;int, ExecutorConfigSchema&gt;` keyed by ExecutorType integer value (post-rename per Wave 2). Include the display name + tier prefix per FR-22 if cheap.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Document forward-compat strategy">
      How does the canvas handle an unknown `Type` value? Falls back to read-only JSON view + warning per FR-27 (`unknown executor type` pattern). Document this is the same pattern.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Raise endpoint URL naming question">
      Does `GET /api/ai/playbook-builder/executor-config-schemas` align with existing PlaybookBuilder endpoint convention? If not, list a recommended alternative + raise as Open Question in design doc. Do NOT decide unilaterally.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Write design document">
      Create `notes/spikes/getconfigschema-design.md` answering all 7 goal items + the endpoint URL question. Include 1-2 worked examples (one for AiAnalysis rich schema, one for placeholder).
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 030 status complete; advance current-task.md to task 031.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Commit">
      Commit `notes/spikes/getconfigschema-design.md` with conventional message. No PR yet — Wave 3 ships as a single PR at task 036.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read (interface + patterns + ADRs)</tool>
    <tool>Grep (search for existing PlaybookBuilder endpoints for URL convention reference)</tool>
    <tool>Write (design document)</tool>
    <tool>Bash (git commit)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="document">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/getconfigschema-design.md</output>
    <output type="state-update">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/current-task.md (advance to task 031)</output>
    <output type="state-update">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (mark 030 ✅)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Design document exists at notes/spikes/getconfigschema-design.md</criterion>
    <criterion>Document defines GetConfigSchema() method signature (return type, sync/async, parameters)</criterion>
    <criterion>Document defines ExecutorConfigSchema + ConfigFieldDescriptor records with JSON serialization names</criterion>
    <criterion>Document enumerates allowed Type values (string, number, boolean, object, array if in v1)</criterion>
    <criterion>Document specifies placeholder/empty schema shape</criterion>
    <criterion>Document specifies endpoint payload aggregation (keyed by ExecutorType integer)</criterion>
    <criterion>Document specifies forward-compat behavior for unknown types (warning state per FR-27 pattern)</criterion>
    <criterion>Document either confirms working endpoint URL or raises naming as Open Question (does NOT decide unilaterally)</criterion>
    <criterion>Document includes 1-2 worked examples (rich + placeholder)</criterion>
    <criterion>current-task.md updated to point at task 031 as next</criterion>
    <criterion>TASK-INDEX.md shows 030 ✅, 031 🔲 ready</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
